## 🐛 Bug Report
Lib version: 4.4.0

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->
Logical bug in worksheet.js in lastRow. 
lastRow doesn't account for possible 'undefined' rows at the end of the table after they are removed with a spliceRows() call. To fix we can use _lastRowNumber which excludes the undefined rows:

## Current function

```javascript
  get lastRow() {
    if (this._rows.length) {
      return this._rows[this._rows.length - 1];
    }
    return undefined;
  }
```

## Suggested fix

```javascript
  get lastRow() {
    if (this._lastRowNumber) {
      return this._rows[this._lastRowNumber - 1];
    }
    return undefined;
  }
```

I also suggest renaming _lastRowNumber to something like _rowCount to be more accurate.
